[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_ar7ve")
reagent_id = "Ca"
title = "Calcium"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Symbol:[/cell][cell]Ca[/cell]
[cell]Element:[/cell][cell]Calcium[/cell]
[cell]Atomic number:[/cell][cell]20[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]40 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]Solid metal[/cell]
[cell]Color:[/cell][cell]Silvery-gray[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Important properties[/b]
• A reactive alkaline earth metal.
• Reacts with water and oxygen.
• Forms many important compounds and minerals.
[b]Where calcium is found[/b]
• In limestone and chalk (CaCO₃).
• In bones and teeth of living organisms.
• In many minerals and rocks.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Important for building materials (cement, lime).
• Used in metallurgy.
• Calcium compounds are used in agriculture and construction.
[b]Safety[/b]
Calcium metal reacts with water and moisture, so it must be handled carefully."
